<br>
And tell us ahead of time that that's what's going on.  <br>
<br>
IF, however, the point is to TEST our response to a crisis (as in a spam drill), then I think that my suggestion above still holds.<br>
<br>
I'm interrupting myself to point out again the distinction between this board and Ex Isle.  The members on THIS board have issues with authority figures being set up in a member community, and the admin's ability to &quot;test&quot; the mods makes them authority figures.  It goes against what we signed up for.<br>
<br>
And, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>HF</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> nobody is trying to influence me - I'm not in private conversation with anyone about this.  I'm just reading all the threads, and getting aggravated with the issue.  NOT because it's a trifling issue, but because we seem to be missing the spirit of the issue for looking at the letter of it.  <br>
<br>
AT HEART, this board is about trusting people to make sound judgement, and respecting one another. <br>
<br>
AT HEART, it is about NOT having authority figures dictating how things are done, and protecting the membership from such a dictatorship ever arising.<br>
<br>
AT HEART, our policy is not about rules, but about limits.  Unless I misunderstood things.  Which is possible.  <br>
<br>
But if that's the case, then we have to be respectful when someone says &quot;you are infringing on my sense of freedom.&quot;  We are going through some growing pains, as we get used to having this freedom, but I'd like for those growing pains to yield productive results.  I'd like for it NOT to result in us growing increasingly stringent and pointing at policy... because we will lose the war that way.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>HF</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> I agree that you don't have to ask the membership everytime you want to do something.  But the membership is pushing back on a decision you made.  It is our right.  We need to be heard, and some consensus needs to be reached.  I will abide by any final decision, cheerfully.  BUT, I will also fight with all that I've got to protect the sacred idea of this board....<br>
<br>
<br>
