HF's test pissed me off.  No question.  It would have pissed me off no matter who did it but the fact that HF did it made me even angrier because the truth is, I don't LIKE HF (and he knows it and we discussed it when he was first asking me to take this job).  I thought that I'd be able to do an objective job despite the fact that I don't like him.<br>
<br>
I was wrong.  I can't so I quit.  It's not the test itself that prompted this but the fact that, as I have long suspected and actually told you guys:  I ain't cut out for a moderating job.  In this context I 've got too much baggage.  <br>
<br>
So while I appreciate the support from Connie the truth is that it was a bad idea in the first place.  It's okay, now I can say I tried it.  Not everyone is cut out for every job.<br>
<br>
I'm a much better advocate or watchdog than I am a mediator/facillitator.  We all have our strengths and weaknesses.<br>
<br>
And btw, I like QT's suggestion.<br>
